      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "First real release. The 1.0.x tags before this were shakeout builds while I got CI and the Obsidian review pipeline working.\r\n\r\nLaunch terminal commands, applications, or websites from Obsidian, each one gets its own command and hotkey. Ships with Claude Code pre-configured as the default launcher.\r\n\r\n- Three launcher types: terminal, app, website\r\n- Per-OS terminal picker (macOS, Windows, Linux), plus a custom launch template override for anything else\r\n- Loads on mobile; website launchers work there, terminal/app fail gracefully instead of crashing",
